      • result

        public final MesosEventClient.ClientStatusResponse.Result result

    • Method Detail

      • footprint

        public static MesosEventClient.ClientStatusResponse footprint(boolean hasNewWork)
        Tells the caller that this client is deploying the service's footprint. This may either be an initial deployment or a re-deployment following a configuration change, either of which may involve changing the service footprint. This does NOT include in-place restarts of failed tasks, nor launches of sidecar tasks which were already allocated. This code has two purposes:
        • Allow upstream to detect a stalled deployment (cluster too small, or other misconfiguration)
        • Allow a multi-service scheduler to only have one service deploying at a time, to prevent deadlocks if the cluster doesn't have enough free room for multiple simultaneous services

      • launching

        public static MesosEventClient.ClientStatusResponse launching(boolean hasNewWork)
        Tells the caller that this client is launching tasks into existing footprint. This may either be initial deployment of tasks into a previously acquired footprint, or restarting tasks into prior footprint, or launching sidecar tasks into prior footprint.

      • idle

        public static MesosEventClient.ClientStatusResponse idle()
        Tells the caller that this client has no work pending and does not need to receive offers right now. However it should continue to receive any task statuses that are relevant to it.

      • readyToUninstall

        public static MesosEventClient.ClientStatusResponse readyToUninstall()
        Tells the caller that this client has finished running and can be switched to uninstall mode. The caller should long-decline any unused offers.

      • readyToRemove

        public static MesosEventClient.ClientStatusResponse readyToRemove()
        Tells the caller that this client has finished uninstalling and can be torn down. After this is returned, the caller may then notify the client of framework deregistration by calling MesosEventClient.unregistered(), but this is not required. This status is only relevant to multi-service schedulers.
